sequenceDiagram
    participant User as User Browser
    participant Router as OpenShift Router<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS1.2+
    participant Route as Workbench Route<br/>Edge TLS
    participant Service as Workbench Service<br/>8888/TCP HTTP
    participant Pod as Workbench Pod<br/>JupyterLab
    participant PyPI as PyPI Mirror<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant S3 as S3 Storage<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant Git as Git Repository<br/>443/TCP HTTPS

    Note over User,Git: Flow 1: User Accesses Workbench
    User->>Router: GET https://workbench-url<br/>Auth: OAuth/Bearer Token
    Router->>Route: TLS 1.2+ Termination
    Route->>Service: HTTP/8888<br/>Token forwarded
    Service->>Pod: HTTP/8888<br/>Internal routing
    Pod-->>Service: JupyterLab UI (HTML)
    Service-->>Route: HTTP Response
    Route-->>Router: HTTP Response
    Router-->>User: HTTPS Response<br/>JupyterLab Interface

    Note over Pod,PyPI: Flow 2: Install Python Package
    Pod->>PyPI: GET /simple/package<br/>HTTPS/443 TLS 1.2+
    PyPI-->>Pod: Package files
    Pod->>Pod: Install to filesystem

    Note over Pod,S3: Flow 3: Access S3 Data
    Pod->>S3: GET /bucket/data.csv<br/>HTTPS/443 TLS 1.2+<br/>Auth: AWS IAM/Access Keys
    S3-->>Pod: Data file

    Note over Pod,Git: Flow 4: Clone Git Repository
    Pod->>Git: git clone https://...<br/>HTTPS/443 TLS 1.2+<br/>Auth: Git credentials
    Git-->>Pod: Repository files
